Yoruba Nation Activist, Chief Sunday Adeyemo, better known as Sunday Ighoho, has been released by the Government of the Republic of Benin. Daily Independent gathered that the activist was released to the leader of the Umbrella body of Yoruba Self-determination Groups, Ilana Omo Oodua Worldwide, Professor Banji Akintoye and a French Language Expert/ Deputy Alana of Ilana Omo Oodua Worldwide, Professor Wale Adeniran on Monday. Akintoye confirmed the release of Sunday Igboho in a press statement issued by the group Communication Secretary, Mr Maxwell Adeleye Sunday Igboho: Afenifere Condemns Extenson Of Incarceration Igboho Will Soon Return Home, Lawyer Hints The Yoruba group described the release of Ighoho as a Triumph of Truth over Darkness in Yoruba Land. Details later